programme.desc: A beautiful pair of 18th-century breech-loading pistols breach the shop; a seller brings in a paperweight made by renowned glass artist Paul Stankard.

programme.desc: Rolling into Buena Park with their crew, Brandi and Jarrod pick up what may be the best of the worst; Kenny and his cousin glide through a half decent locker.

programme.title: Jesus: His Life E1
programme.desc: Judea is occupied in a time of turbulent unrest. Joseph, a craftsman, faces a test of faith in Nazareth, when his fiancee Mary tells him she is expecting a child, who is the Son of God.

programme.title: Jesus: His Life E2
programme.desc: Jesus's life intersects with that of John the Baptist, a radical preaching in the desert against Judea's rulers. John baptizes Jesus, starting his divine mission, but loses his own life.

programme.title: Crimes That Shocked Asia S2E2
programme.desc: In this episode, we look at some of Asia's most infamous kidnappings and see how when negotiations break down, things can turn ugly very quickly.

programme.title: The Pickers S13E234
programme.desc: Mike and Frank accept a special invite from Indiana's Model-A Ford lady and fall hard for her ultra-rare barn-fresh Model-A tow truck.

programme.title: Car SOS S7E9
programme.desc: Tim and Fuzz travel to Jersey in the Channel Islands to take on a 1972 Ford Escort Mexico. Owner Gary has been recovering from a horrific spell of ill health, having been struck down with both blood cancer and tuberculosis, and his family hope that his restored classic will give him a new lease of life. Once the boys get the car back to the workshop they quickly realise that not one single part of the car is salvageable.

programme.title: China Relics Decoded E1
programme.desc: China is the world's oldest living civilization. But as the nation modernizes, there's a new thirst to rediscover its roots. Historian Sam Willis unravels how Chinese fascination with the sky has influenced peoples and cities from the past to the present, creating a lasting understanding of the relationship between heaven and earth.

programme.title: Explorer S3E12
programme.desc: Phil Keoghan journeys to Zambia to help tag lions. Francesca Fiorentini investigates the cause of a rash of earthquakes in Oklahoma. Cara Santa Maria explores if we are breeding dogs to death. Ryan Duffy joins Cory Booker as he uncovers environmental racism. Jago Cooper reveals risks to the global chocolate supply and solutions underway to save it.

programme.title: Hostile Planet E3
programme.desc: Step inside the most frigid habitat known to Earth - the poles. Here, the planet's ultimate survivalists include whale-hunting polar bears, leopard-seal dodging penguins and a pack of Arctic wolves that bring down a pair of musk oxen. Polar species have evolved bodies and behaviours that help them combat the intense hostility of their habitats. But now, their world is changing so fast - literally breaking apart under their feet - and their resilience will be tested beyond the extreme.

programme.title: Mega Factories: Supercars E8
programme.desc: The rule-breaking and revolutionary Nissan GT-R competes with the big boys from the supercar world using a combination of cutting-edge aerodynamics, hi-tech engineering and a handcrafted V6 engine. It's one of the most affordable supercars on the road – mass produced on a production line in Nissan's Tochigi mega factory.

programme.title: India's Mega Kitchens S1E1
programme.desc: Can a single meal brighten a child's future? Can a school lunch bridge the gap in education? Let's go back to school with the Akshaya Patra Foundation and learn how the world's largest school lunch program is cooking up millions of meals and offering India's children a hopeful tomorrow, one plate at a time.

programme.title: Explorer S3E13
programme.desc: Phil Keoghan journeys to North Carolina to see the science behind Nascar racing. Jago Cooper explores a chilling new discovery of human sacrifice. Francesca Fiorentini investigates what DNA tests actually tell you. Tim Samuels reveals a new probiotic made from the human gut.

programme.title: Dictators Rulebook E3
programme.desc: A study of the methods used by Italian dictator Benito Mussolini to rise to power and turn Italy into the first fascist state. A master of propaganda, he dubbed himself 'Il Duce' (the leader) and delivered bombastic speeches in which he idealized a fascist culture and promised to return Italy to the grandeur of Ancient Rome. Instead he created a one-party dictatorship and kept his grip on power for two long decades.

programme.title: Mega Air E7
programme.desc: Mega Air follows the challenging journey of a 55-million-dollar batch of cancer pharmaceuticals, from Northern Ireland to Heathrow, for a flight to the US. An East Midlands Airport wildlife officer gets into a flap trying to scare birds from his runway. Two gigantic stone crushing machines, destined for an African mine, threaten to crush the monster Antonov 124 air freighter. We travel with a pushback driver at one of America's busiest cargo airports.

programme.title: Hidden Gems Of Turkey E2
programme.desc: To uncover Turkey's hidden gems, Digital Nomad and travel enthusiast Andrew Evans heads to Western Anatolia and the Aegean Region. Following the same ancient trade routes trodden by oriental trade and spice merchants thousands of years ago, he finds a treasure trove of ancient wonders. From mysterious mountain top statues to some of the most pristine Roman remains in the world, Andrew uncovers the secrets of ancient Turkey.

programme.title: Running Wild With Bear Grylls E3
programme.sub-title: Zachary Quinto In The Panama Jungle
programme.desc: Bear Grylls and actor Zachary Quinto race the clock to traverse a dense Panamanian jungle before an impending storm makes landfall. Their adventure begins with a helicopter ride, but once dropped off deep in the brush, they must rely on a primitive navigation technique to help them reach their extraction point- but it won't be easy! From massive cliffs and steep ravines to an underground river cave and an old crashed plane, there are obstacles at every turn!

programme.title: India's Mega Kitchens S1E3
programme.desc: Watch as a sacred mega kitchen gears up to feed over 100,000 devotees in a single day for the annual festival of Lakshadeepotsava in the temple town of Dharmasthala.

programme.title: Mega Factories: Supercars E2
programme.desc: Let's take a rare look inside the Corvette Mega Factory which produces the ZR1 – a genuine American supercar. It's the fastest, most powerful, and most expensive Corvette ever built and it can compete against the best that Europe has to offer.

programme.title: Mega Air E8
programme.desc: Mega Air gets up close to the most bizarre air freighter on the planet, the bulbous Airbus Beluga, a flying whale that swallows entire aircraft wings. We chart the misfortunes of a wealthy, American classic car enthusiast, airfreighting one of the earliest cars ever built to a famous UK car rally; and, to much fanfare, global mega movers, UPS take delivery of a brand-new Boeing 747-8, the largest freighter made in the US.

programme.title: Hidden Gems Of Turkey E3
programme.desc: National Geographic's Digital Nomad Andrew Evans completes his journey across Turkey in search of hidden gems by crossing the Bosphorus to the European side of Istanbul. Here, he immerses himself in the city's multicultural heritage, exploring how the city's unique location and complex history have shaped Istanbul today. Getting lost in its streets, he brings us a colourful picture of the city today.

programme.title: Dictators Rulebook E4
programme.desc: An exploration of the methods and tactics of Generalissimo Francisco Franco, who controlled Spain with absolute power for four decades. Employing violence and terror learned in colonial warfare, Franco led the 1936 military coup that overthrew the legitimately elected government and went on to rule the nation as his personal fiefdom until his death in 1975. The mass graves of his victims are being exhumed to this day.

programme.title: Mega Factories: Supercars E2
programme.desc: Let's take a rare look inside the Corvette Mega Factory which produces the ZR1 – a genuine American supercar. It's the fastest, most powerful, and most expensive Corvette ever built and it can compete against the best that Europe has to offer.

programme.title: Hidden Gems Of Turkey E3
programme.desc: National Geographic's Digital Nomad Andrew Evans completes his journey across Turkey in search of hidden gems by crossing the Bosphorus to the European side of Istanbul. Here, he immerses himself in the city's multicultural heritage, exploring how the city's unique location and complex history have shaped Istanbul today. Getting lost in its streets, he brings us a colourful picture of the city today.

programme.title: Dictators Rulebook E4
programme.desc: An exploration of the methods and tactics of Generalissimo Francisco Franco, who controlled Spain with absolute power for four decades. Employing violence and terror learned in colonial warfare, Franco led the 1936 military coup that overthrew the legitimately elected government and went on to rule the nation as his personal fiefdom until his death in 1975. The mass graves of his victims are being exhumed to this day.

programme.title: Mega Factories: Supercars E2
programme.desc: Let's take a rare look inside the Corvette Mega Factory which produces the ZR1 – a genuine American supercar. It's the fastest, most powerful, and most expensive Corvette ever built and it can compete against the best that Europe has to offer.

programme.title: India's Mega Kitchens S1E3
programme.desc: Watch as a sacred mega kitchen gears up to feed over 100,000 devotees in a single day for the annual festival of Lakshadeepotsava in the temple town of Dharmasthala.

programme.title: Mega Air E8

programme.title: Nazi World War Weird E1
programme.desc: Robert Joe & Dr. Sam Willis are on a mission to uncover the secrets behind Heinrich Himmler's Wewelsburg Castle in Germany. The mystery shrouding the castle has given birth to bizarre pop culture fantasies. As RJ and Sam fill in the blanks of this mystery they visit other sites that Himmler was linked to in an attempt to reveal the depths of Himmler's mind.

programme.title: Hostile Planet E4
programme.desc: The planet's hottest habitats - our deserts - are getting even hotter, drier and bigger, yet a host of remarkable animals still survive in the harshest conditions, including cunning hyenas, pint-sized meerkats and sand-dwelling spiders. Follow their lives through a single day in the desert to appreciate how they deal with the sun's formidable power as it grows stronger with every passing minute.

programme.title: Nazi Megastructures: America's War E1
programme.desc: June 1944. The Japanese are in retreat across the Pacific. Now, at the island of Saipan, they face a pivotal battle. If they lose, a deadly new American weapon - the B-29 long-range bomber - will be within range of Japan for the first time. But the Empire believes a mighty weapon of its own will win the battle - a deep-rooted tradition of aggression and sacrifice in battle. Can the Japanese warrior mindset prevail?

programme.title: Gok's Chinese Takeaway E1
programme.desc: Gok travels around Barcelona and seeks Western Mediterranean cuisine in this episode. He attempts to make Barcelona sausages with the help of a professional artisan sausage maker. Also, Gok looks for the renowned Chinese restaurant in the territory where peking duck and dim sum are served distinctively in Spanish-style with its original appearance.

programme.title: Nazi World War Weird E2
programme.desc: 10 May 1940, thanks to the blitzkrieg the Nazis capture Belgium's most impregnable fortress, Fort Eben Emael, in less than 15 minutes. Dr. Sam Willis and Robert Joe investigate the victory and discover that a performance enhancing drug called Pervitin, an earlier version crystal meth, might have been fueling the Wehrmacht in their march over Europe.

programme.title: Locked Up Abroad S12E9
programme.desc: Australian hippy, Mark O'Brien is dissatisfied with life. He joins an ashram in India, lead by the infamous guru Osho, looking for enlightenment. But when a fellow disciple encourages Mark to join her in a plan to smuggle an exotic form of hash to Amsterdam, it sets of a chain of events that leads him to a very different commune; the notorious Yawanda Central Prison.

programme.title: Drain The Oceans S2E9
programme.desc: An expedition searches for the iconic wrecks of the Battle of the Pacific, including the ship that delivered the Hiroshima bomb, USS Indianapolis.

programme.title: Nasca Lines: Unlocking The Secrets
programme.desc: As Peruvian archeologists along the site of the famed Nasca Lines employed hi-tech drones to look for signs of looting and encroachment, they were surprised to discover new designs made by an older Paracas culture - originating before the time of Christ. New footage expands on these Paracas geoglyph discoveries even further, diving deeper to explore the theory of whether these glyphs were meant to glow under the light of a full moon.

programme.title: Running Wild With Bear Grylls E4
programme.desc: Actress, supermodel, and social media influencer Cara Delevingne realizes a long-held dream of accompanying Bear Grylls on an adventure. Sweeping Cara off her scooter and onto a helicopter, the two ascend into the mountains of Sardinia. At nearly a mile high in elevation, Bear shows Cara how to brave several heart-stopping obstacles including pulling herself across a horizontal line suspended 200 feet in the air and a dangerous waterfall rappel.

programme.title: Gok's Chinese Takeaway E2
programme.desc: Gok's journey begins with Elizabeth Chong, a local food guru and an author who traces back to her grandfather in the 1850s for family recipes. She teaches Gok the frugal dishes like Steamed Egg Custard and Lap Yook Potatoes. Inspired by local gastronomy, Gok returns to his own kitchen and creates an Aussie-Asian feast as a tribute to this city.

programme.title: Nazi Megastructures: America's War E2
programme.desc: September 1944. The Japanese have suffered catastrophic defeats across the Pacific. Wasting men in a futile attempt to expel the enemy at the beach is no longer viable if they are to protect the Home Islands. On Peleliu the Japanese build an island-wide defensive megastructure that creates a killing zone unprecedented in the Pacific. What unfolds is one of the most brutal battles of World War Two. Americans are killed in their thousands.

programme.title: Drain The Oceans S2E10
programme.desc: In this story of Hitler's vision to conquer the world using his high-tech battleships, Drain the Oceans reveals the rise and fall of the Third Reich's deadly fleet.

programme.title: Petra: Secrets Of The Ancient Builders
programme.desc: In the heart of the Jordanian desert, the ancient city of Petra is full of mysteries. How was this architectural prowess achieved more than 2,000 years ago?

programme.title: Locked Up Abroad S12E10
programme.desc: Texan cousins Paris and Marlon always fancied themselves as entrepreneurs. When Paris' dad offers them the opportunity to run a car wash in Lima, Peru, they jump at the chance. But Peru has a dark side and the boys have no idea their ambitions to make money are leading them into grave personal danger. Ahead of them lies incarceration, attempted murder and the ultimate family betrayal.

programme.title: Alien Deep With Bob Ballard E3
programme.desc: Dr. Robert Ballard is on a global quest to unravel one of the world's biggest mysteries, where did life on Earth begin? Ballard suspects that life may have started where hot rock and water collide in one of the world's most seemingly hostile environments, active volcanoes deep within the ocean. He hunts for answers in the Mediterranean.

programme.title: Hostile Planet E5
programme.desc: Delve beneath the surface of the largest habitat on Earth - our oceans - to uncover a world of extraordinary extremes from crushing depths to stormy coasts and vast blue deserts to crowded reefs. Oceans are dynamic environments where animals must adapt to life of constant change. Discover how seals fend off sharks; how turtles risk their lives to create their next generation; and how ingenious orca fight to survive in the face of ever-increasing competition.

programme.title: Scrapyard Supercar E1
programme.desc: Ralph and his 2 teams of petrolheads aim to build scrap cars to beat Shane's iconic Porsche 911 Turbo in an acceleration challenge.

programme.title: Hidden Gems Of Turkey E1
programme.desc: National Geographic digital nomad Andrew Evans gets under the skin of Eastern Turkey, travelling from the ruined city of Ani to the stone circles of Gobekli Tepe, considered the world's oldest temple. Travelling the same roads that oriental spice and silk traders used for thousands of years he discovers how the many civilisations that passed through the region have left their mark on the food, culture and architecture of modern Turkey.

programme.title: Alien Deep With Bob Ballard E4
programme.desc: Dr. Robert Ballard and a team of scientists search for answers regarding recent phenomenon occurring in the ocean. Waves may be getting bigger, ocean patterns may be shifting, and seas are rising. They investigate alarming waves that defy gravity, uncharted deep-sea currents, and alien creatures that move as much ocean as the winds.

programme.title: Airport Security: Peru E7
programme.desc: Police rush to handle a rare incident on a domestic flight: something suspicious in a Serbian citizen's bag. Agents find liquid cocaine disguised in drink bottles in another man's bag. A passenger without luggage reappears carrying a suitcase and agents rush to investigate. Counterfeit cash is uncovered in the mail facility.

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S19E9
programme.desc: LAM Mozambique Airlines Flight 470 is headed for Luanda, Angola, when it disappears from radar. Rangers in a remote Namibian park eventually discover the wreckage, and NTSB investigators join a local team for their largest-ever case. The wreckage provides the first major clue, and after ruling out a host of possible causes, investigators are left with an chilling conclusion.

programme.title: Live Free Or Die S3E3
programme.desc: It's trapping season and frontiersman Colbert must get to work. Selling beaver pelts in town will provide him with the bulk of the money to pay the taxes on his land and purchase small items that he cannot get from the swamp. Hunter-gatherer Matt tries hunting rabbits with his new homemade bow and arrow. If he cannot get a source of protein to store for the winter he will need to leave in search of a new shelter.

programme.title: Running Wild With Bear Grylls E5
programme.desc: Golden Globe-nominated actor Armie Hammer pairs with Bear Grylls to scuba dive in search of an underwater sea cave reportedly used by smugglers somewhere off the coast of Sardinia. Along the way, Armie battles his paralyzing fear of heights and samples some local delicacies-and things take an unexpected turn when he gets hijacked in the middle of the expedition.

programme.title: Hidden Gems Of Turkey E2
programme.desc: To uncover Turkey's hidden gems, Digital Nomad and travel enthusiast Andrew Evans heads to Western Anatolia and the Aegean Region. Following the same ancient trade routes trodden by oriental trade and spice merchants thousands of years ago, he finds a treasure trove of ancient wonders. From mysterious mountain top statues to some of the most pristine Roman remains in the world, Andrew uncovers the secrets of ancient Turkey.

programme.title: Scrapyard Supercar E2
programme.desc: Ralph and his 2 teams of car buffs build scrap cars to try and outbrake Shane's Jaguar F-Type SVR.

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S19E10
programme.desc: Taking off during a major storm, a brand-new 737 falls from the sky over West Africa, and an international group of investigators soon descends on Cameroon. Submerged in mud and water, Kenya Airlines Flight 507 crashed into a mangrove swamp, killing everyone on board. And while investigators ultimately pinpoint one fatal mistake that triggered the tragedy, they also uncover a lethal cascade of issues that sent the passenger jet spiralling toward the ground.

programme.title: Live Free Or Die S3E4
programme.desc: Homesteaders Tony and Amelia begin construction on a solar dehydrator to preserve their abundance of deer meat. With its design existing solely in Tony's mind, the pair must skillfully piece together various recycled and repurposed materials to build the apparatus in such a way that it capitalizes on all the solar energy it can.

programme.title: Airport Security: Peru E8
programme.desc: Police stop a woman travelling with her 5-year-old. If she's a carrier, agents must figure out what to do with the child. A Mexican citizen is found with a large amount of beer and soft drinks. All these goods may contain cocaine. Officers uncover a creative new method of hiding cocaine in food packaging.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E15
programme.desc: The village of Medhaghat in Assam- home to the Bodos, was soaked in festivities on Pablo's arrival. People dressed in vibrant clothes, environment filled with all sorts of food aromas, Medhaghat was a perfect destination for some gala time. Pablo fished, cooked and gorged on some exceptional food with the Bodos.

programme.title: Fearless Chef E9
programme.desc: The Fearless Chef endures death-defying and claustrophobic conditions when he visits the coastal region of southwest Sri Lanka on the hunt for fresh tiger prawns and a naturally fermented palm wine.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E45
programme.desc: Ben heads to Clover Hill his favourite sparkling wine vineyard in Australia to take a look at their new cellar door. Here he uses some pork belly from a recent dinner service to create a pork belly and grain salad which he matches with a glass of Chardonnay. At the University of Queensland, Ben and Joel throw a Mexican twist onto a scrambled eggs dish.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E46
programme.desc: Ben and the crew are back down in the Tarkine at the Bonorong Tarkine Trails base camp. Ben fires up the Oz Pig and makes a super cheesy penne dish in the wok. Up in Queensland, Ben heads to The University of Queensland Lakes where he cooks up some Mexican hot dogs inspired by his Chihuahua's back at home.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita's Mexican Fiesta E10
programme.desc: Let's travel to the cloudy forests of Chiapas near the border with Guatemala where Peter explores a state with the highest indigenous population in Mexico and with it, some of the most interesting food yet.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita's Mexican Fiesta E9
programme.desc: Peter Kuruvita arrives in the Mayan stronghold of the Yucatan Peninsula, major producer of one of the hottest chillies on earth - the Habanero, before heading to the state of Tabasco where chocolate has been consumed for thousands of years.

programme.title: My Pacific Quest E2
programme.desc: Adventurer Ellis Emmett reaches the Kingdom of Tonga, the first stop on his ambitious Pacific sailing quest. Ellis befriends a local named Lofi, and the two set sail for the isolated island of Tofua. Along the way they explore a newly formed volcanic island, navigate treacherous coral reefs, and must hunt for their dinner.

programme.title: Dive Detectives E6
programme.desc: The Fletchers penetrate the wrecks of the Hamilton and the Scourge to find out why they sank and why so many lives were lost.

programme.title: Sara's Australia Unveiled E7
programme.desc: After touring the outback, Sara arrives in Melbourne and discovers a bar which can only be accessed through a secret door and a cinema overlooking the city's skyscrapers at night. Then, she joins the local community in an annual polo game where city slickers and rural cowboys compete on their riding skills. Finally, she finds out the secret of Michelin-star quality wagyu beef from the stockmen.

programme.title: Sara's Australia Unveiled E8
programme.desc: Sara drives along the Great Ocean Road and arrives in surf country - Victoria. She discovers a supreme olive oil and reveals the secrets behind the peppery flavor. Surrounded by a vast array of vegetables and fruits, Sara decides to pay tribute to the fresh and natural ingredients by dishing up a salad using indigenous pistachio, local wine and peppery olive oil.

programme.title: John Torode's Malaysian Adventure E9
programme.desc: John is in Ipoh, where local guide Peggy Lim takes him on a gastronomic journey in the city's historic area. After sampling Malaysian cuisine unique to this region, he delves into the kitchen of Chef Tan Chuan Ho to find out the secrets behind an Ipoh classic, Hainanese Chicken Rice. Back in the UK, John visits the home of renowned chef Ping Coombes and learns how to bake crispy golden kaya puffs.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E15
programme.desc: The village of Medhaghat in Assam- home to the Bodos, was soaked in festivities on Pablo's arrival. programme.title: Korean Soul Food
programme.desc: With a sound reputation of being healthy, balanced and flavorsome, Korean food has drawn global attention and attracted people around the world to visit the bustling capital city, Seoul. In the company of actress Eun-Hye Park, we'll be revealing the taste and history of a variety of popular Korean dishes, including samgyetang and bibimbap, as well as investigating their healthy cooking principal.

programme.title: Sara's Australia Unveiled E9
programme.desc: Sara strolls down memory lane and ranks her top five moments in Australia. From Melbourne, Darwin to Broome and Victoria, she prepares unforgettable delicacies like lamp chop and octopus bashing. Also, she savors unique cuisines like pizza made by alfresco oven. Other than cooking, Sara spends time with a group of kangaroos feeding on grass and also witnesses an alligator hunting for food.

programme.title: San Diego: More To Explore E1
programme.desc: Seventy miles of coastline, near perfect weather, and an exciting urban center, there's always an adventure to be had in California's first city. With an endless bucket list of opportunities, it'd be hard to find a better vacation destination. Soar through the skies, uncover hidden speakeasies, and step aboard a 16th century ship- discover what makes San Diego a city of Adventure.

programme.title: John Torode's Malaysian Adventure E10
programme.desc: John arrives on the beautiful Island of Langkawi where he receives a step-by-step guide on making the famous Malaysian dish, duck rendang. He also makes his way to one of the most exclusive hotels on the island and helps chef Rihizul Othman cook up a tantalizing dish of grouper bakar samba, against a sublime backdrop of the talcum-powder beach of Datai Bay.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E16
programme.desc: A 700-year-old village of the Angami Nagas is a perfect example of a close-knit community. Pablo gets a glimpse of their community culture visiting a community house followed by a community kitchen where he devours on some exotic Naga food. What surprised Pablo the most about this tribe was their transformation from fierce headhunters to farmers.

programme.title: Fearless Chef E10
programme.desc: The Fearless Chef, Kiran Jethwa, visits the legendary headhunters of Borneo, the Iban tribe, to face a grueling hunt through thick jungle in search of wild boar, edible frogs and palm hearts.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E55
programme.desc: Ben ventures back to the beautiful Tarkine Rainforest in Tasmania's far North-West, where he cooks a simple dessert, Charred Stonefruit with Ginger. Back at The University of Queensland, Ben is joined by Dr. Joel Gilmore. Here they discuss a very controversial topic - why some people don't like coriander and the science behind it.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E56
programme.desc: Ben makes the most of a beautiful sunny day to make a Cherry, Chocolate and Salted Caramel dessert in his own backyard. Then Ben heads back to The University of Queensland and meets up with Dr. Joel Gilmore, where they cook Mexican hotdogs that are inspired by Ben's pet dogs.

programme.title: Gordon Ramsay: Uncharted E1
programme.desc: High in Peru's Sacred Valley of the Incas, Chef Ramsay is a man on a mission, travelling by motorbike to unlock the secrets of high altitude cuisine.

programme.title: Living Free With Kimi Werner E1
programme.desc: Champion spear fisher Kimi Werner visits a woman living a largely subsistence way of life and learns about her lifestyle. She's in pursuit of a deep truth about what it means to live more simply, more freely, and with a closer connection to nature.

programme.desc: Champion spear fisher Kimi Werner visits a woman living a largely subsistence way of life and learns about her lifestyle. She's in pursuit of a deep truth about what it means to live more simply, more freely, and with a closer connection to nature.

programme.title: Somewhere In China E4
programme.desc: Peter and Jeff Hutchins visit the Chinese province of Yunnan, which contains the largest ethnic diversity in China. 25 minority groups live in the province, and the brothers visit the National Ethnic Minorities Park to learn about and hopefully understand these cultures. To further immerse themselves, they also explore native villages and take part in games, ceremonies and festivals.

programme.title: Eat: The Story Of Food E4
programme.desc: Christopher Columbus. Julia Child. Clarence Birdseye. These are some of the revolutionary men and women who have changed what and how we eat, remaking not just food history but human history. Some of these food revolutionaries are well known, others obscure. But one thing they have in common is that they have fundamentally shaped how we live today.

programme.title: Route Awakening S1E6
programme.desc: The journey winds through the cradle of Chinese civilization in Shanxi and Shandong. Harry meets a bamboo lantern maker, whose craft is considered one of the intangible cultural heritages of China. He also discovers a kind of ancient housing where people lived in silo caves. As he makes his way to Shandong, Harry helps fishermen to catch and sell shrimp, followed by making giant kites in Weifang.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita's Mexican Fiesta E9
programme.desc: Peter Kuruvita arrives in the Mayan stronghold of the Yucatan Peninsula, major producer of one of the hottest chillies on earth - the Habanero, before heading to the state of Tabasco where chocolate has been consumed for thousands of years.

programme.title: Sara's Australia Unveiled E9
programme.desc: Sara strolls down memory lane and ranks her top five moments in Australia. From Melbourne, Darwin to Broome and Victoria, she prepares unforgettable delicacies like lamp chop and octopus bashing. Also, she savors unique cuisines like pizza made by alfresco oven. Other than cooking, Sara spends time with a group of kangaroos feeding on grass and also witnesses an alligator hunting for food.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E1
programme.desc: Like the carnival festivals of Rio and Venice, Goa marks the days before Lent with an all-out celebration: three full days of eating, drinking, and partying. David takes part in all of the festivities, including an appearance on a float in Panjim's annual Carnival kick-off parade. He ends up spending time with some Italian expats and celebrating the holiday Venetian-style.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E47
programme.desc: Ben makes a healthy Salmon Poke Bowl and heads down to Huon Aquaculture to see where his salmon has been farmed. Up at The University of Queensland, Joel joins Ben to make a King Fish and Green Olive Dressing, Joel talks to Ben through why fish skin contracts when you place it in a hot pan.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E48
programme.desc: Ben heads to the brand new Clover Hill cellar door in Northern Tasmania and cooks an Asparagus and Roasted Tomato Penne with a paired with glass Clover Hill Vintage Sparkling. Up at the University of Queensland, Ben and Joel prepare a King Fish Sashimi with an easy pickled salad. Back in the studio Ben shows us how to cook one of his favourite cuts of meat, the rump cap paired with some crispy cheesy potatoes.

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E5
programme.desc: Turpan, nicknamed the world's sweetest city, is the next leg of Jamie's culinary journey. After lending a hand at a vineyard, and learning what makes these grapes so highly prized, he will risk it all to discover the local secret of what makes this China's largest grape growing region. He also will find the top chefs to teach him three of his favourite Chinese dishes and make a Turpan inspired feast to celebrate the end of harvest.

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E6
programme.desc: In this episode, Jamie is at his last stop on the silk road journey, Urumqi, the capital of Xinjiang. He will spend time with the lovely Kazakh friends in the mountains and experience an amazing array of ethnically diverse foods from Kazakh horsemeat to Uyghur baked buns. He will get an exclusive lesson in making everybody's favourite noodle dish and to top it all off, he will cook his own dishes for the most important festival in the Islamic calendar.

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S7E7
programme.desc: Whilst renovating their garage, Steve and wife Marie never dreamt that they would find a World War Two bunker hidden underneath their garden. They decide to revolutionise the damp and dark space into a home office. Steve has devised an ingenious motorised lift that will lift the roof and let in light. Better still when the bunker is not in use the roof goes down and they keep full use of the garden and you'd never know what lies beneath.

programme.title: Somewhere In China E5
programme.desc: Peter and Jeff Hutchins visit with the Buddhist monks of China. Buddhism was once the dominant religion, and the brothers will explore the traditions of the monks, from the yellow hat Tibetans to the rainforest temples of the Dai Buddhists. Despite the many changes in the country, these traditions are still thriving.

programme.title: Eat: The Story Of Food E5
programme.desc: Throughout history, mankind has been on a mad-dash to satisfy our prodigious sweet tooth and consume vital energy. Along the way sugar helped build empires and even fueled the Industrial Revolution. From the time sugarcane was first refined in India, to our newest high-tech candy factories, we've been developing newer and better delivery systems for the taste we can't live without.

programme.title: Don't Tell My Mother S3E9
programme.desc: Diego explores where past and present collide in the biggest city in the world, Tokyo. Japan is one of the most technologically-advanced places on the planet, and in the richest city in Asia, the line between reality and fiction seems thin. From the wild to the traditional, the classic to the outlandish, discover Tokyo like you've never seen it before.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita's Mexican Fiesta E10
programme.desc: Let's travel to the cloudy forests of Chiapas near the border with Guatemala where Peter explores a state with the highest indigenous population in Mexico and with it, some of the most interesting food yet.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E2
programme.desc: Formerly a colony of Portugal, Goa still has a large Portuguese population, and nowhere is their influence more evident than in the local cuisine. David is on a mission to discover Goa's unique blend of Portuguese and Indian cultures, one dish at a time. He also learns about the Toddy Vinegar that gives many dishes their signature Goan touch.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E3
programme.desc: David heads out on a crab fishing expedition with some local fishermen in a nearby river. Afterwards, he meets up with an internationally-renowned chef Cyrus Todiwala, who takes him to the local fish market to check out what is on offer. Later, David gets a chance to explore Goa's famous beach shack culture and ventures into Calamari, a renowned seafood restaurant, to flex his culinary muscles.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E57
programme.desc: Ben heads back to Clover Hill Winery in Tasmania's North-East, to cook Beef Cheek Sliders. Here Ben meets with Adam Torpy, who tells us a bit about their new building and how it reflects the surrounding landscape. Ben then heads to The University of Queensland where he meets up with Dr. Joel Gilmore. Here Ben teaches us how to create his Never Fail Meringue dessert.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E58
programme.desc: Ben heads down to his local beach, the Mersey Bluff to create his version of the Prawn Cocktail. Up at The University of Queensland, Ben recreates the pumpkin soup from his first book, Mexican Craving. In the studio Ben makes a bite sized burger, the perfect canape dish.

programme.title: Around The World In 80 Dishes E1
programme.desc: Manu Feildel is a household name in Australia as co-host of the smash-hit My Kitchen Rules, as well as being an award-winning chef and author. He challenges himself to circumnavigate the world, to relive his favourite book “Around the World in 80 Days”, through his food-loving eyes. Will he start his journey from Australia to Dorset via London on time and within budget?

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S7E8
programme.desc: John, a tailor from London dreams of creating his own office space in the garden so he can spend more time closer to home, after the arrival of a newborn baby. Sadly, John's DIY skills might not be up to the job! So he recruits his old friend Stephen to help him design and build a tailor's studio he'll be proud to bring his clients to.

Just before leaving the port of Venice, some passengers lose their luggage but the ship must leave on time to keep up the itinerary. Next, the missing luggage issue takes an ominous turn. A guest who recently had a kidney transplant needs his medication that is thought to be in the missing luggage.

programme.title: Heathrow S4E3
programme.desc: Heathrow is currently the busiest airport in Europe so medical emergencies and busy check-ins are the norm. Add in half term with rich Russian kids returning home from British boarding schools, and the biggest mobile crane stopping in the middle of a live airfield, and tonight's episode of Heathrow's Britain's Busiest Airport won't disappoint.

programme.title: Heathrow S4E4
programme.desc: All things Eastern feature in this week's episode of Heathrow: Britain's Busiest Airport. Be it the arrival of some special cargo, a potential people trafficker flagged to Border Force, or the polar vortex that battered Britain in March affectionately called the beast from the east. Rookie Ian is also back – this time wielding a gun.

programme.title: Celebrity Chef: East Vs West E5
programme.desc: The neck and neck competition reaches its climax as the chefs arrive in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia for the Grand Finale.

programme.desc: Ben sets up in the gardens at Fairholme to cook one of his favourite Mexican dishes, fajitas with a pineapple and chipotle twist. programme.title: Food Lab S2E50
programme.desc: Ben and the crew are at the Harvest Market in Launceston, the market which has won Australia's Most Outstanding Farmers Market in 2013 and 2017. Here Ben picks up some fresh produce and has a chat with Simon, one of the Harvest representatives to talk about the famous market and what makes it so great.

programme.title: Bangkok Airport E5
programme.desc: What is it like to be stranded at Bangkok Airport? A panic attack grounds a young Aussie tourist in departures, a Swedish backpacker is savaged by a dog, and concern grows for the safety of a young Indian traveler.

programme.title: John Torode's Malaysian Adventure E9
programme.desc: John is in Ipoh, where local guide Peggy Lim takes him on a gastronomic journey in the city's historic area. Back in the UK, John visits the home of renowned chef Ping Coombes and learns how to bake crispy golden kaya puffs.

programme.title: Cruise Ship Diaries S1E4
programme.desc: Nomadi, a famous band, is set to perform a rock concert in the theatre of the Costa Serena. Security has to be beefed up to handle difficult fans and paparazzi. But the day has not started out well as the ship arrives in Venice late due the thick mist, and there is less time to prepare before the next boarding of the German passengers and the rock stars.

programme.title: Heathrow S4E5
programme.desc: 80% of all visitors to Britain arrive by air, and today's episode of Heathrow begins at 04:49 with the arrival of a 17 hour non-stop flight from Perth. Border Force pull over a Ghananian business man declaring 114 grand in cash, and there's love in the air, with a blind date at the romantic venue of T5 arrivals, and the end of an era on the airfield for Chief Trainer Simon.

programme.title: Heathrow S4E6
programme.desc: Royal and celebrity feature in the last episode of Britain's Busiest Airport, with Terminal 5 receiving a very special visitor and Buggy Driver Carlo getting star struck. British Airways have a new robot on the airfield and Borderforce release the hounds in search of dirty money.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita Coastal Kitchen S2E1
programme.sub-title: What The Region Is Famous For
programme.desc: Chef and Restaurateur Peter Kuruvita begins a new culinary adventure in the extraordinary region of Margaret River; discovering a world of food, wine and colourful characters along the way.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita Coastal Kitchen S2E2
programme.desc: Peter continues his journey throughout Margaret River meeting extraordinary artisanal producers of the region and using their ingredients in a host of delicious dishes.

programme.title: Eat: The Story Of Food E6
programme.desc: What we eat and how we eat today has changed so much that our great grandparents would hardly recognize it. We spend less of our time on food than ever before. How did this happen and what does it mean? Guilty Pleasures explores modern food and its uneasy relationship between convenience and quality.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E59
programme.desc: Ben and Rhys begin their Tamar Farm Gate tour at Bridgenorth Berries, a new and small Berry Farm on within the East Tamar region of Tasmania. Here Ben chats to one of the owners Narelle about the extensive berry variety they grow. At The University of Queensland Ben and Joel create the perfect Mexican breakfast dish.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E60
programme.desc: Ben and Rhys stop at Langdale Farm in the East Tamar Region of Tasmania to meet with Oli, pig farmer and bacon smoker extraordinaire. At The University of Queensland, Ben and Joel create their own science experiment by making a tangy lime sherbet. In the studio Ben creates a Wasabi Slaw which teams perfect with a steak.

programme.title: Bangkok Airport E6
programme.desc: An unhappy tourist tries to strangle an airport official and a Full-Moon party goes wrong for two young British girls while the English Thai boxing team flies in to fight for the world championship. As political unrest sweeps the country and threatens to close down the airport, Captain Jack, the happiest man in the immigration department, finally stops smiling.

programme.title: Heathrow S4E6
programme.desc: Royal and celebrity feature in the last episode of Britain's Busiest Airport, with Terminal 5 receiving a very special visitor and Buggy Driver Carlo getting star struck. British Airways have a new robot on the airfield and Borderforce release the hounds in search of dirty money.

programme.title: John Torode's Malaysian Adventure E10
programme.desc: John arrives on the beautiful Island of Langkawi where he receives a step-by-step guide on making the famous Malaysian dish, duck rendang. He also makes his way to one of the most exclusive hotels on the island and helps chef Rihizul Othman cook up a tantalizing dish of grouper bakar samba, against a sublime backdrop of the talcum-powder beach of Datai Bay.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S2E9
programme.desc: Fabio Lisboa, a lifelong fish enthusiast, is looking to make his dreams come true. His vision is a 5000-gallon tank full of sharks. An aquarium that size will not only take up over half of his office, but will be the largest private tank in South Florida. As always, Living Color is up to the challenge.

programme.title: Wild 24 S2E6
programme.desc: Wild 24's journey around the South Seas takes you through the Tropics, South America, and Antarctica. From deadly reefs and a nesting turtle's race to the ocean to a starving baby seal waiting for its mother, this voyage also looks closely at the feeding frenzy whales and penguins which need to put on blubber to survive the harsh winter.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S6E1
programme.desc: To catch a deadly Black mamba, Simon must face his biggest fear - heights! And to save a spitting cobra, he deals with his OCD and digs in a poo pit!

programme.title: Animal Fight Club S5E3
programme.desc: In this episode of Animal Fight Club, nature gets nasty as the animal kingdom prepares for wild-life warfare. Using remarkable footage, gathered from the world's leading nature documentary makers; combined with stunning, 'under the skin' CGI, we reveal the strategies, techniques and weaponry used when animals fight for their bloodline and survival.

programme.title: Savage Kingdom S3E3
programme.desc: After the murder of one of their own, the Makulu Pack of Wild Dogs looks to a new leader for salvation. The Western Pride is exiled to the fringes the Kingdom as they fight to protect their cubs from enemies on all sides. And as the marauding hyena clan commits the cruelest of acts, their ferocious commander Mmamotse reveals her soft side as she swells her ranks and trains a new army.

programme.title: Hostile Planet E2
programme.desc: Grasslands are some of the most volatile lands on the planet, where animals must endure a seasonal cycle of flood, famine, freeze and fire. We reveal the extraordinary challenges these animals must overcome, and how our changing world is making survival even tougher than before. From epic battles between wolves and bison, to nail biting showdowns between cheetahs and Thompson gazelle fauns, this is an epic tale of life and death in the planet's most dramatic wildernesses.

programme.title: Shark Men S2E3
programme.desc: The Expedition team takes a trip into the unfamiliar, cold, dark, and Jellyfish-infested waters near the Farallon Islands and Big Slur, California. In the murky waters of this protected marine sanctuary, they are facing some of the biggest sharks they have ever encountered, and things are not going to plan.

programme.title: Wild 24 S3E4
programme.desc: In the mystic river - the Nile, wildlife like hippos, crocodiles, lions, wolves, mole rats and lungfish pull out all stops to survive. When the river flows, the backdrop changes from mountain to rainforest; when the water retreats, the habitat turns from swamp to desert. No one can defy the forces of nature.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S6E3 !
programme.sub-title: There's A Snake In The Fridge
programme.desc: Snakes in the City is a documentary-style reality TV series centering on the daily life of snake rescuers, Simon Keys, and his herpetologist girlfriend, Siouxsie Gillett in the coastal city of Durban, South Africa. This once was a tropical jungle teaming with spitting cobras, green mambas, black mambas, pythons, night adders, bush snakes and boomslangs: it's their territory and humans built a city right on top of it. There is a snake in nearly ever home so Simon and Siouxsie, experts in animal behavior, hunt down and capture by hand, the world's most dangerous and venomous snakes that emerge every summer. They then release these problem snakes back in the wild away from humans. Every call out is a chance to save a snake's life and with this being his busiest time of year, they're on cal.

programme.title: Animal Fight Club S5E4
programme.desc: This killer episode of Animal Fight Club reveals how some of the most dangerous fights in the animal kingdom are between the same species, whether for territory, bloodline or survival. It also shows the amazing escape techniques fighters use to escape death. Top wildlife film makers and user generated footage from around the world prove that from top predators to the smallest insects, life is a constant battle - and there can only be one winner.

programme.title: World's Weirdest S1E1
programme.desc: Take a deep dive into the realm of creepy aquatic creatures to uncover the world's most bizarre water-dwelling tenants. In this episode a fish with a transparent head shows everything it's got. A master-of-disguise octopus camouflages itself to capture prey or elude pursuit. A lizard literally walks on water and a fish walks on dry land... and that's just for starters!

programme.title: Untamed Philippines E2
programme.desc: Moving from turtles of the Palawan coast to the unique National Marine Park at Tubbataha, to meet giants, whale sharks and manta rays. On Bohol we explore the Chocolate hills and met the man who has done more than anyone else to help the Philippine tarsier, a tiny, bug-eyed primate. We also see how people can mediate between people and wildlife as we join a snake hunting team catching and translocating a deadly Samar cobra. On Cebu we join the crowds that come to swim with whale sharks, explore the island home of the sea krait and thrill to see a pelagic thresher shark. On Mindanao we visit a family that have been caring for the endemic Philippine sailfin lizards for many years, so long in fact, that they get 160 or more turning up for breakfast. On Samal island we see the world's greatest concentration of Geoffroys Rousette fruit bats and learn of their value to local farmers. In the South of Mindanao we end with the most iconic Philippine animal of all, the majestic Philipp.

programme.title: Shark Men S2E4
programme.desc: The Great White team finds themselves in troubled waters when the Sanctuary Super Intendent refuses to return their emails or calls, putting the future of the entire research trip in jeopardy. The crew can't do anything but wait for clarification from the authorities and the suspense and stress is taking its toll.

programme.title: Wild 24 S3E5
programme.desc: Alaska is a frost-bound place where bears, whales, salmon, orca, walruses and beavers are racing the seasons, trying to make the most out of the brief summer. They need to spend time every day to save food energy for a rainy day because the return of icy darkness will cut off their food supply and leave them to starve.

programme.title: Dr Oakley: Yukon Vet S6E8
programme.desc: Dr. Oakley participates in a race pitting human runners against reindeer, five muskox undergo pregnancy tests, and Daisy participates in a family reunion.

programme.title: Unlikely Animal Friends S4E4
programme.desc: Here comes another 3 pairs of special friends you've never seen before: a wild fawn who is friends with a dog, an autistic four-year-old child who comes out of his shell with the help of his feathered friends (a flock of chickens), and a cat that's friends with a rat.

programme.title: World's Weirdest S1E3
programme.desc: Get ready to brush feathers with the freakiest birds in the world as we take to the sky. Check out dancing manakins that do the moonwalk, shrikes impaling their prey before ripping it apart, and lyrebirds singing snazzy solos. Some of the freaks don't even need wings for takeoff - flying squirrels, flying snakes, and carps springing from the water to knock people out, will blow your mind.

programme.title: Wild Cambodia
programme.desc: We take you to wild Cambodia, where the extreme monsoon weather systems have created one of the most unique ecosystems on the planet. This ancient land was once ruled by a great empire, yet life here is dictated by an unforgiving weather system, from a life-sucking dry season to wet season defined by floods, shaping an incredibly diverse wildlife that you should not miss.

programme.title: Wild 24 S3E1
programme.desc: It is a 24-hour journey through the kingdom of big cats, where cheetahs, leopards, jaguars and lions out-hunt and out-compete the rest of the animals to hold their place at the top of the food chain. Stealthiness, cunningness and power are the symbols of big cats. The felines are merciless in the battlefield because every hunt is a calculated kill for them.

programme.title: Frozen Islands E1
programme.desc: In the Southern Atlantic and Indian Oceans, between the latitudes of 40 and 60 degrees South, there is a scattering of tiny, inhospitable islands that are crucial to the survival of millions of marine creatures that use these islands to breed. South Georgia, Bouvet, Marion and Crozet Islands are home to some of the world's largest populations of Elephant Seals, Antarctic Fur Seals, Wandering Albatross, King and Macaroni Penguins. These creatures, superbly adapted to life in a freezing ocean need to come ashore to mate and raise their young. And where there are millions of animals there are the hunters that follow: Killer Whales.

programme.title: The Naked Superhero
programme.desc: Looks aren't everything. Despite its appearance, the Naked Molerat should be envied. It lives to a very old age, never gets sick, and is practically impervious to pain. Scientists want to know why. In the quest to combat age-related illness - and even ageing itself - researchers around the world are searching for the Methuselah gene in this remarkable rodent to find cures for humans.

programme.title: Shark Men S2E5
programme.desc: The lengths to which the Expedition team will go to for science is astonishing. They face hazards such as injury, harsh weather conditions, leaking or, in the worst case, sinking boats and have to endure all this in the home of some of the most ferocious marine predators in the world. All of this for an ever elusive giant female Great White Shark.

programme.title: Wild 24 S3E6
programme.desc: A battle for survival takes place on the ancient isles of the East Indies, a land where dragons still roam, big apes hold sway over jungles and the rarest big cats hunt. Battles are won and lost while life comes and goes every single day in this evolutionary melting pot.

programme.title: Frozen Islands E2
programme.desc: The islands found in the Southern Indian and Pacific Oceans are so remote that man hardly ever sets foot on them. They're some of the most inhospitable places on Earth, but they are crucial to the survival of some of the world's rarest creatures. Southern Right Whales breed in the bay of Auckland and Enderby, New Zealand Seal Lions and Yellow-eyed penguins use the beaches and forests. Royal Penguins nest only on the island of Macquarie and the Royal Albatross uses the slopes of Campbell Island. And where there are breeders there are hunters: Killer Whales and Giant Petrels.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S6E5
programme.desc: Sioux comes face-to-face with a Green mamba, Simon is almost bitten by a Black mamba and they catch two bizarre snakes that don't belong in Durban!

programme.title: Snakes In The City S6E6
programme.desc: A huge black mamba hides under the kitchen sink, Simon rips apart a couch to find a spitter and climbs a tree to catch a highly-venomous vine snake.

programme.title: The Miracle Cheetah
programme.desc: Born a wild cheetah in South Africa's North West province, Sibella's life nearly ended at the hands of hunters. Lying at death's door, fear and mistrust haunting her eyes, she was fortunate enough to be rescued by the De Wildt Cheetah and Wildlife Trust. In December 2003, Sibella began a new chapter when she was flown to Samara along with two male cheetah. Eleven years on, Sibella has outlived most cheetah in the wild, proving herself to be a capable hunter despite the occasional twinge from her previous injuries.

programme.title: Rough Cut
programme.desc: Saat seorang bintang film menyewa sesosok gangster untuk menjadi lawan mainnya demi menghindari skandal setelah menghajar aktor lainnya hingga nyaris tewas, ia tak menyangka akan menghadapi sosok nan mematikan.

programme.title: Shoot Me In The Heart
programme.desc: Dua pemuda bertemu di sebuah rumah sakit jiwa. Soo-myung mengalami trauma karena sang ibu bunuh diri dan Seung-min dimasukkan secara paksa ke sana meskipun ia waras. Bagaimanakah jalinan takdir mereka?

programme.title: Wonderful Nightmare
programme.desc: Akibat kesalahan di surga, seorang pengacara nan tak percaya cinta tewas dalam kecelakaan mobil. Guna menutupi kesalahan mereka, ia harus hidup sebagai ibu rumah tangga selama sebulan demi kembali ke kehidupan lamanya.

programme.title: We Are Brothers
programme.desc: Dua kakak beradik yang terpisah sejak lahir bersatu kembali 30 tahun kemudian dan melakukan perjalanan untuk mencari ibu mereka yang menderita Alzheimer.

programme.title: Will You Be There?
programme.desc: Keinginan terakhir seorang ahli bedah adalah bertemu almarhum kekasihnya. Ia menerima pil yang bisa membawanya kembali ke masa lalu untuk menyelamatkan kekasihnya. Di sana, ia bertemu dengan dirinya di saat muda.

programme.title: Countdown
programme.desc: Seorang penagih utang menderita kanker hati dan harus mendapatkan transplantasi hati dalam sepuluh hari. Seorang penipu bersedia mendonorkan hatinya jika ia bisa melacak pria yang memasukkannya ke dalam penjara.

programme.title: Sunset In My Hometown
programme.desc: Ketika seorang rapper yang kurang sukses kembali ke kampung halamannya untuk mengunjungi ayahnya yang sakit, ia bertemu kembali dengan teman-teman dan keluarganya yang ia tinggalkan dulu.

programme.title: The Mayor
programme.desc: Byeon Jong-gu, walikota Seoul, mencalonkan diri sebagai presiden. Ia menggunakan segala cara untuk menyembunyikan rahasia-rahasia tergelapnya dari publik yang menyukainya.

programme.title: The Battleship Island
programme.desc: Selama pemerintahan kolonial Jepang, sekitar 400 warga Korea diwajibkan untuk bekerja di Pulau Hashima. Ketika rahasia kelam pulau itu terungkap, para pekerja Korea berencana untuk melarikan diri.

programme.title: Dark Figure Of Crime
programme.desc: Terinspirasi dari kisah nyata, film ini menceritakan tentang sebuah pertarungan psikologis nan sengit antara seorang detektif polisi dan seorang pembunuh yang mengaku telah melakukan beberapa pembunuhan.

programme.title: The Magician
programme.desc: Seorang pesulap muda nan berbakat jatuh cinta pada seorang putri yang bertunangan dengan mantan gurunya. Hal ini menyebabkan sebuah pertikaian sengit antara dua pesulap nan hebat.

programme.title: Coffee Mate

programme.title: Love Now
programme.desc: Hubungan yang saling berkaitan di antara dua pasang kekasih terjalin. Bagaimanakah mereka menjalani dan memperbaiki hubungan nan berbahaya dan rahasia ini?
